:::summary
Nutrition is the science of how living organisms obtain and use the chemical compounds found in food to sustain life, support growth, and maintain health. As a discipline it spans biochemistry, physiology, medicine, and public health. For Christians, the care of the physical body carries theological weight: Paul reminded the Corinthians that "your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit" (1 Corinthians 6:19–20), and the Latter-day Saint revelation known as the Word of Wisdom offers one of the most specific scriptural treatments of diet and health in any religious tradition.
:::

